com.objetdirect.tatami.client.dnd
Interface IDnDBehavior<E extends IDnDElement,S extends IDnDSource<?>,T extends IDnDTarget>

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractDnDBehavior, DnDDefaultWidgetBehavior, DnDGenericBehavior, WidgetDnDBehavior
public interface IDnDBehavior<E extends IDnDElement,S extends IDnDSource<?>,T extends IDnDTarget>

Author:
rdunklau This interface defines a drag and drop behavior. A drag and drop behavior is usually attached to a drag and drop source. A drag and drop source can handle dnd events by itself, but it is recommended to delegate it to a behaviour, which can be common to multiple source. Implement this interface to listen for drag and drop events.
See Also:
DnDElement}, IDnDSource}, Target}

Method Detail

onDrop

boolean onDrop(java.util.Collection<E> dndElements,
               S source,
               T target,
               java.lang.String targetNodeId,
               boolean isCopy)
Triggered when one or more dnd elements are dropped on a target. This is where you should implement your DOM modification after the drop. (Maybe moving a widget from one place to another ...)

Parameters:
dndElements - : Collection of the dropped DnDElements
source - : the dnd Source object from which the DnDElements are originated
target - : the dnd Target object containing the drop location.
targetNodeId - : Id of the DOM element on which we drop, inside the dnd target (can be null, or anything).
isCopy - : wether the nodes should be copied or moved. This flag is usually set up by the user pressing "Ctrl" key while dragging.
Returns:
: true if the drop has been accepted, false otherwise
